comments: Turner (IND) moves alongside Highsmith's (MIA) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Nembhard (IND) establishes himself in Adebayo's (MIA) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Turner (IND) moves alongside Adebayo (MIA) and marginal body contact occurs during his upward shooting motion.
Oladipo (MIA) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Nembhard (IND) as they come together during the drive.
Oladipo (MIA) delivers body contact to Brissett (IND) that affects his SQBR during the drive.
Lowry (MIA) establishes himself in Hield's (IND) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Turner (IND) makes contact with Herro's (MIA) arm, which affects his jump shot attempt.
Lowry (MIA) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Nembhard (IND) as they come together at the end of the drive.
Lowry (MIA) touches the ball last before going out of bounds.
Adebayo (MIA) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Brissett's (IND) layup attempt.

Lowry (MIA) reaches back and makes some contact with Turner's (IND) head as he pursues the rebound.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Lowry (MIA) and Turner (IND) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Nembhard (IND) touches the ball last before going out of bounds.
Strus (MIA) maintains his arms within the frame of his body and does not deliver illegal contact to McConnell (IND) during the screen.
Adebayo (MIA) continues to re-establish himself following the initial contact and creates further contact with Turner (IND) that affects his ability to defend over the screen.
